title: Bitcoin Trend Analytics October 13
name: BitMidas
contents:
BTC is about to leave the downward channel . If CPI is lower than expected, it will jump out of the channel; otherwise, BTC drops and prolongs the movement within the channel. Strength is contracting, cultivating a breakout that is likely to happen upon the release of CPI .

Yesterday BTC ran between the speculative area at $18798.44 and intraday resistance at $19275.64. The capital inflow held the pressure from bears. This will keep going until a high volatility moment at 20:30(UTC+8). As volume shrinks, intraday support and resistance are fragile today, which is more prominent as the release time approaches. Use today’s intraday target points prudently.

The expected CPI figure is 8.1%:
if data <8.1%, BTC rebounds
If data >8.1%, BTC drops
If data =8.1%, BTC goes sideway

The market expected interest rate hike in November: 75bp(15.2%),50bp(84.8%)
Comment: $18798.44 is diverted to $18763.03

title: Risk-Off, 13th October 2022
name: mrstockyetoro
contents:
🖼 Daily Technical Picture 📈

➤ Minor down day in US indices. Pre-market was firmly positive until the PPI (Producer Price Index) numbers were released. It showed persistent inflation in the costs of production. These costs can be passed on to consumers and therefore feeds into CPI /Consumer inflation numbers.

➤ With CPI numbers coming out Thursday/today, we should expect a jump in volatility . I have no idea what the inflation number will be but there are bullish signs that I am willing to take some risk for a potential upside move.

➤ I further reduced my remaining short NASDAQ position to -10% and added long exposure of +40% with STOXX50 and German DAX . An overall small +30% long exposure. I think this is a sensible level of risk use given market conditions. The maximum portfolio exposure is +/- 200% on capital, the level of highest conviction.

➤ Conclusion: I'm risk-on for a move higher but also risk-off by taking a lower exposure than previous days. Manage your risks.

title: 🌊 XRP  NEXT DIRECTIONAL WAVE FORMING 🌊
name: Rocksorgate
contents:
🌊XRP's next wave is forming and let's just start from our last idea post which you can also find below and read before continuing!


🌊In the previous idea I pointed out how we were still trading within that channel we'd had down for a bit and it can be seen where that mountain fall started as encircled, we exited that mountain directly forth moving off as a skier does getting ready to parachute down and lost our relatively new marked channel. Once that 200 EMA and channels are lost as we keep noting it can start these big directional moves and that brought us to one of our already marked channels so we can trust that this is a strong channel.

🌊On top of that we're already seeing this big move already starting up which has formed over the short time that I've started writing this idea! So I'm happy to see that happening and see our markings doing the job absolutely stunning' as they should. What you guys will want to do now is look on the lower time frame's using our EMA"s and see whether or not we manage to reclaim that 200 EMA and really get the push we need. Otherwise we could get a rejection by which then we could possibly see the fall extend further if we fall below 0.485 so note that.

🌊Leaving the idea here for now but markings do their job as usual and you can always come back and press that play button to get what's next and possibly in play and leave a like and follow to keep posted as usual. Thanks for tuning in, sorting a lot out a always but managing what I can for you guys, thank you.

~ Rock '

title: SPY double diamond in 1H chart w/ divergence near Oct low
name: xtremerider8
contents:
SPY formed 2 diamond patterns as seen in this hourly chart. It formed slight RSI positive divergence near the Oct low. However, this divergence may still get lower to reach 3500, an impt Fibonacci level, more so if the CPI report come out higher tomorrow.
Weekly wma 200 still the line in the sand.
The next major catalysts this week are Thursday”s CPI data & bank earnings . Start of earnings season will
usher in more volatility next week due to the fear of earnings recession.
Not trading advice
Comment: Market dumped & pumped today which is not unusual for Diamond patterns.
